XPATH
Traversing : travelling from one element to another ,done in dynamic elements
2 types of traversing:
-> forward (parent to child)
-> backward (child to parent)   /.. we will reach parent of that

-> locate dynamic element there are 2 way 1. via parent 2. via sibling


** locating via parent
1. identify static element
2 . move to common parent (means move to parent common to static and dynamic elements)
3. from common parent fetch the dynamic element


example://td[text()="Gentry"] it is fetching Gentry column
        //td[text()="Gentry"]/.. it is fetching parent element of td that is tr
        //td[text()="Gentry"]/..//td[6] now this will fetvh the 6th element of that row

text is the property to fetch the value

